        "front": "What is body temperature regulation?",
        "back": "The process by which the body maintains its internal temperature within a narrow range.",
        "icon": "thermometer"
      },
      {
        "front": "Why is body temperature important?",
        "back": "It is crucial for optimal enzyme function and overall metabolic processes.",
        "icon": "importance"
      },
      {
        "front": "How does the hypothalamus contribute?",
        "back": "It acts as the body's thermostat, detecting changes and initiating responses.",
        "icon": "brain"
      },
      {
        "front": "What are the mechanisms of heat production?",
        "back": "Metabolism, muscle activity, and hormonal regulation contribute to heat generation.",
        "icon": "heat"
      }
    ]
  }
